#
# Log retention period (in days) - DEBUGGING INFRASTRUCTURE
#
# Captures stderr output from all commands to .log/ directory.
# This is NOT a production logging system - it's debugging infrastructure
# similar to VPN_SWITCH_TRACE_FILE but captures stderr instead of execution flow.
#
# Behavior:
#   > 0: Debugging enabled - stderr logged to .log/YYYY-MM-DD/HHMMSS.PID_function.log
#     0: Debugging disabled - stderr redirected to /dev/null (silent mode)
#
# Log file organization:
#   .log/
#   ├── 2025-10-26/
#   │   ├── 140523.12345_wireguard_start1.log
#   │   └── 140524.12346_wireguard_connect1.log
#   └── 2025-10-25/
#       └── ...
#
# Cleanup:
#   vpn-switch validate     # Warns about logs older than retention period
#   vpn-switch logs clean   # Generates rm commands for old logs (review first)
#   vpn-switch logs clean | sh  # Execute cleanup
#
# Default: 1 day (enable debugging during initial setup when most issues occur)
#
# Debugging workflow:
#   - Enable LOG (=1) + TRACE (=1) when debugging issues
#   - LOG captures errors, TRACE captures execution context
#   - Together they provide complete debugging information
#   - Disable both (=0) for production/silent mode
#
# Customization examples:
#   VPN_SWITCH_RETENTION_DAYS_LOG=7     # Keep 1 week
#   VPN_SWITCH_RETENTION_DAYS_LOG=14    # Keep 2 weeks
#   VPN_SWITCH_RETENTION_DAYS_LOG=0     # Disable (silent mode)
#
# Note: Each command creates its own timestamped log file. The retention period
# applies to entire date directories, not individual files.
